  "prompt": "Can people see if you have viewed their instagram?",
  "response": "Whether or not people can see if you've viewed their Instagram content depends on the type of content:\n\n*   **Instagram Stories:** Yes, if the account is public or if you follow the account. When you view an Instagram Story, the account owner can see your username (or name, depending on their settings) in the list of viewers. This list is visible for 24 hours, until the Story disappears.\n\n*   **Instagram Reels:** Yes, similar to Stories, if the account is public or if you follow the account. When you view an Instagram Reel, the account owner can see your username (or name, depending on their settings) in the list of viewers.\n\n*   **Instagram Posts (Photos/Videos on the Feed):** No, Instagram does not show the account owner a list of who has viewed their regular posts. The only indication of engagement is through likes and comments.\n\n*   **Instagram Profile:** No, people cannot see if you have simply visited their profile page.\n\n*   **Instagram Live:** Yes, the account owner can see the number of viewers during the live broadcast, and they can see the specific users who are watching.\n\n**In summary:**\n\n*   **Visible Views:** Stories, Reels, Live videos\n*   **Invisible Views:** Profile, Posts (photos/videos on the feed)",
